  "description": "An enzyme is a protein (or, in rare cases, an RNA molecule) that catalyzes a specific chemical reaction — it speeds the reaction up without being consumed in the process. Nearly every chemical reaction in a living [cell](./cell.md) is catalyzed by an enzyme. Without enzymes, [metabolic](./metabolism.md) reactions would occur too slowly to sustain life.",
